    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-13T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4164: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-13T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 13, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Your 45, February 13, 4 p.m. I have just received this telegram.</p>
                <pb facs="0426" n="322" xml:id="pg_322"/>
                <p>Referring to paragraph 2, I desire that you endeavor at once to enlist the
                    support of your British and French colleagues in joint or concurrent protest
                    against the proposed landing of any of these troops in the International
                        Settlement.<note n="35" xml:id="d340fn35">For the Consul General’s action,
                        see his telegram No. 48, February 14, noon, <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_192">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 192</ref>. For the Japanese reply, see
                        telegram No. 92, February 21, 11 a.m., <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_198">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 198</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
